UID:302@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260501
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260502
SUMMARY:BWA Y4b: Bilingual Books Sent Home (4B & 5B)
DESCRIPTION:School books for pupils in classes 4B and 5B are sent home for parents to review before Parent Teacher meetings.\n\nIn preparation for upcoming Parent Teacher meetings, teachers are sending student books home for review. For classes 4B (Y4b) and 5B (Y5b), books are sent home on Friday 1st May.
CATEGORIES:ACADEMIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:303@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260505
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260506
SUMMARY:BWA Y4b: Deadline -  Return Books (4B & 5B)
DESCRIPTION:Deadline for pupils in classes 4B and 5B to return their school books for the English focus week.\n\nAll books sent home on May 1st for classes 4B (Y4b) and 5B (Y5b) must be returned to school today, Tuesday 5th May, for the English focus week.
CATEGORIES:ACADEMIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:304@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260420
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260421
SUMMARY:BWA Y4b: Deadline -  Sign up for Bilingual Parent-Teacher Meetings
DESCRIPTION:Deadline to complete the Ecole de Wix sign-up link for the upcoming bilingual stream parent-teacher meetings.\n\nParents and carers of pupils in the bilingual stream (RB, Y1B, Y2B, Y3B, Y4B, Y5B, and Y6B) must complete the sign-up link provided by Ecole de Wix by today to secure a time slot for the summer term parent-teacher meetings. BWA will subsequently send out Zoom link details ahead of the allotted meeting times.
CATEGORIES:ADMIN
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:310@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260505
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260506
SUMMARY:BWA Y4b: Bilingual Parent-Teacher Meetings (Y4b/CE2B)
DESCRIPTION:Video conference parent-teacher meetings for class Y4B/CE2B.\n\nParent-teacher meetings for the bilingual Year 4 class (CE2B) will be held via video conference (Zoom). Meetings will run throughout the school day. Parents should have received a sign-up link from Ecole de Wix. Pupils are still expected to attend school as normal on this day.
CATEGORIES:ACADEMIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:334@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260515
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260516
SUMMARY:BWA: International Families Day
DESCRIPTION:School-wide celebration of diverse heritage including a homework project, national dress day, and an after-school international buffet.\n\nInternational Families Day at BWA. Pupils are invited to complete a heritage homework project (due 11th May). On 15th May, pupils may wear national dress or flag colours. Parents are invited to volunteer to share culture/skills (form due 8th May). An international buffet will be held in the lower hall from 3:30pm; food donations requested (bring to office from 2:30pm). All food must be nut-free.
CATEGORIES:COMMUNITY
END:VEVENT
